acquaint /əˈkweɪnt/

(acquainting,acquainted,acquaints) 

1. V-T If you acquaint someone with something, you tell them about it so that they know it. If you acquaint yourself with something, you learn about it. 使了解 [正式] 

例： Have steps been taken to acquaint breeders with their right to apply for licenses? 已经采取措施让饲养动物者了解他们申请执照的权利了吗？ 

